        <refbodydiv outputclass="summary">
          <section id="summary">roman designates text should not be given any empohasis, such as bold or italic. It is useful for when a parent block element assigns bold, italic, etc., such as a heading. In such cases, the use of roman can actually provide emphasis to the content by making it standout.</section>
      </refbodydiv>
        <refbodydiv outputclass="d4p">
         <section id="d4p">roman is a specialization of ph.</section>
      </refbodydiv>    	    
